\section{Materials and methods}
\label{Sec:Methods}

\subsection{Dataset and severity mapping}
HAM10000 \cite{ref3} comprises 10\,014 dermoscopy images collected at clinical sites in Vienna and Queensland, each carrying one of seven diagnostic labels with structured metadata. We collapse the seven diagnoses into five ordered severity stages, from benign nevi at stage 0 to melanoma at stage 4 (Table~\ref{tab:mapping}). Benign nevi dominate at 66.9\% of the data while the pre-cancerous stage 2 class holds only 3.3\%, a roughly 20:1 imbalance ratio that dictated our sampling and loss-weighting strategy through the inverse-frequency weights $w_{c}=N/(C\!\cdot\!N_{c})$ listed in the table.

