Each sample is described by a 17-dimensional metadata vector. Because 57 records lacked an age value we applied median imputation and normalised to $[0,1]$, adding three binary age-bracket indicators. Biological sex is a single binary feature. The eight most frequent anatomical sites are one-hot encoded with a ninth slot for the remainder, and two modality flags (histopathology and confocal) record the ground-truth provenance. The data were split 70/15/15 with stratification on the severity label, giving 7\,009 training, 1\,502 validation, and 1\,503 test images.

\subsection{Ensemble architecture}
The framework processes each image at three native resolutions in parallel: $380^{2}$ for EfficientNet-B4, $456^{2}$ for EfficientNet-B5, and $384^{2}$ for ConvNeXt-Base. Each backbone $\mathcal{F}^{(k)}_{\theta}$, $k\in\{\mathrm{B4},\mathrm{B5},\mathrm{Cnx}\}$, produces a pooled visual embedding through global average pooling,
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:gap}
\mathbf{v}^{(k)} = \mathrm{GAP}\!\left(\mathcal{F}^{(k)}_{\theta}(\mathbf{X})
\right)\in\mathbb{R}^{d^{(k)}_{v}},
\qquad d_{v}\in\{1792,2048,1024\}.
\end{equation}
The per-backbone metadata branch computes
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:meta}
\mathbf{m}^{(k)} = \mathrm{ReLU}\!\left(\mathbf{W}^{(k)}_{2}\,
\mathrm{BN}\!\left(\mathrm{ReLU}\!\left(\mathbf{W}^{(k)}_{1}
\mathbf{x}_{\mathrm{meta}}\right)\right)\right)\in\mathbb{R}^{32},
\end{equation}
where BN denotes batch normalisation and a dropout of 0.3 is applied before $\mathbf{W}_{2}$. For the ConvNeXt branch the output is widened to 64 dimensions and the ReLU activations are replaced with GELU to match the backbone. The fused representation $\mathbf{z}^{(k)}=\mathbf{v}^{(k)}\oplus\mathbf{m}^{(k)}$ passes through a per-branch classifier head that emits the five-class softmax probabilities $p^{(k)}_{c}$. Figure~\ref{fig:arch} shows the overall layout.

