\subsection{Ablation study}
Removing the ConvNeXt branch costs $-4.65$ pp F1, making it the single most valuable component (Table~\ref{tab:ablation}). Disabling the progressive unfreeze schedule costs $-3.30$ pp, confirming that freshly initialised heads can corrupt pretrained features if not managed. Removing the metadata branches costs $-1.80$ pp globally but, as noted above, nearly 8 pp on stage 2 in isolation. Automatic mixed precision is essentially free on accuracy ($-0.05$ pp) while saving roughly 40\% of the memory footprint, so it is retained.

