\subsection{Visual explanations}
Across the five-stage saliency grid (Figure~\ref{fig:gradcam}), ConvNeXt keeps a tighter focus on the lesion body than either EfficientNet, consistent with its stronger standalone metrics, and where the two EfficientNets err they tend to err together by sliding their attention peak off the lesion centroid. Fusing the maps through Eq.~\ref{eq:fuse} lets the result inherit ConvNeXt's spatial discipline while retaining the EfficientNet feature vocabulary, producing a localisation that no single backbone achieves alone. The fused explanation thus inherits the same variance-reduction property as the probability vote, lifting it from the prediction to the spatial domain.

