\subsection{Limitations}
Three limitations bound any clinical reading of these results. First, the 53.9\% melanoma sensitivity discussed above means the system is unsafe without a clinician in the loop. Second, HAM10000 is drawn from two European sites and skews toward lighter Fitzpatrick skin types, so transfer to darker tones is untested. Third, a five-stage mapping defined on diagnosis codes is a diagnosis-level proxy, not a patient-level one, and cannot encode context such as a benign lesion in an immunocompromised patient that should still be treated urgently. A prospective reader study comparing assisted and unassisted clinician decisions is the necessary step before any deployment claim.

